"Task 1: Change basic bullet or number style\nSubtask 1: Select the list you want to modify\nSubtask 2: Go to the Home tab\nSubtask 3: Click the bullets drop-down arrow for bullet options\n   OR\nSubtask 4: Click the numbering drop-down arrow for number options\n\nTask 2: Change the starting number for numbered lists\nSubtask 1: Select the numbered list\nSubtask 2: Click the numbering drop-down arrow\nSubtask 3: Select \"Bullets and Numbering\"\nSubtask 4: In the dialog box, change the \"Start at\" value to your desired number\nSubtask 5: Click OK\n\nTask 3: Customize bullets with symbols\nSubtask 1: Select the bulleted list\nSubtask 2: Click the bullets drop-down arrow\nSubtask 3: Select \"Bullets and Numbering\"\nSubtask 4: Click \"Customize\"\nSubtask 5: Choose a symbol from the available options\nSubtask 6: Click OK to select the symbol\nSubtask 7: Adjust size and color if desired\n   - Use the size options\n   - Click color dropdown to choose a color\n   - Select \"More Colors\" for additional options\nSubtask 8: Click OK to apply changes"